pageContext.claim: “The World Trade Organization finds that the European Union subsidies to Airbus has adversely impacted the United States, which will now put Tariffs on $11 Billion of EU products! The EU has taken advantage of the U.S. on trade for many years. It will soon stop!”
pageContext.analysis: The tariffs did not immediately go into effect rather, the U.S. Trade Representative released "a preliminary list of EU products to be covered by additional duties." The amount of those duties "is subject to an arbitration at the WTO, the result of which is expected to be issued this summer."
